Columns explanation¶

  • TAA: Alerts (@@ separated)
  • TA: Delay hour (before was in minutes) need to be compared with TIT column
  • TIN: Train Model
  • TIR: Route
  • TSI: Station ID
  • TIM: Direction departura/arrival
  • TIL: Request with parameters
  • TIRE: Destination
  • TIP: Platform number
  • TIT: Departure hour
  • TID: Date
  • TSC: Station Name and ID

def loadFile( _datasetFolder, _dateFolder, _fileName ):
    fullPathFile = _datasetFolder + _dateFolder + '//' + _fileName
    df = pd.read_csv( fullPathFile, engine='python', quoting=1, skip_blank_lines=True,
                     sep=",", quotechar='"',
                     encoding ='utf-8', dtype={'TSI': 'object'}
                    )
    return df.replace(np.nan, '', regex=True)

In [6]:
listDF = []

for dfD in dfsDay:
    df = dfD
    df['TAA'] = df['TAA'].str.strip()
    df['TAA'].replace('', np.nan, inplace=True)
    df.dropna(subset=['TAA'], inplace=True)
    
    bufferDf = pd.DataFrame({ 
        'desc': df['TAA'].values,
        'platform': df['TIP'].values,
        'hour': df['TIT'].values    
    } )
    bufferDf['city'] = df['TSC'].iloc[0].split('%')[0]

    listDF.append(bufferDf)

dfBase = pd.concat(listDF)
dfBase['desc'] = dfBase['desc'].str.replace('Grund: ' , '')

dfBase['platform'] = dfBase['platform'].str.replace('[^0-9]', '', regex=True)
dfBase['hour'] = dfBase['hour'].str.replace('\:[0-9]+', '', regex=True)

# Dont remove duplicates for the density
dfBase= dfBase.drop_duplicates().reset_index()

'''
Some Case-rows contains multiple cases separated by "@@"
Its necessary to split this cases in new rows with the same value in the other columns
'''

dfExt = pd.DataFrame(
    dfBase.desc.str.split('@@').tolist(),
    index=[
        dfBase.city,
        dfBase.platform,
        dfBase.hour
    ] ).stack()

dfExt = dfExt.reset_index()
dfExt.columns = ['city', 'platform','hour','REMOVE','desc']
dfExt = dfExt.drop(['REMOVE',], axis=1)
dfExt['count'] = 1

beforeLength = len(dfExt)

Filtering by min number of cases¶

There are case that just happens in some cities.
To compare the common cases of delay 'unstack' the dataframe and filter by number of indexes.

In [29]:
def filterFct( x ):
    #print(x.index.value_counts())
    # There are 10 cities. Filter the Cases in almost 7 cities
    return len(x.index.get_level_values(1)) > 7

d42 = d41.groupby(level=0).filter( filterFct )

'''
Returns a list of list:
    0 - list of platforms -- [items(int)]
    1 - list of hour-delays --  keys(str):[items(int)])
    2 - dataframe
    
index same in both
'''
def getPlatformDataByCity( _cityName ):
    ps = dfS[ dfS['city'] == _cityName ].set_index('platform')
    platforms = list( set( ps.index.get_level_values(0) + '' ))
    platformsData = { 
        numPlatform : list( ps.loc[ [numPlatform] , ['hour']].stack().values.astype(int) )
        for numPlatform in platforms 
    }
   
        
    return [ 
        [ int(p) for p in platforms],
        platformsData,
        ps
    ]
